description:
FULL RECIPE BELOW. Such an easy recipe that has been my go-to when I want to cook something fast. Delicious with rice, not to mention this is loaded with protein and fiber using very affordable ingredients. Kain na, let’s eat!


INGREDIENTS:
½ kilo tokwa, crumbled
Cooking oil
5 cloves of garlic, peeled, crushed, and minced
2 yellow onions, peeled and chopped
2 tomatoes, chopped
1 ½ cup bean sprouts
2 cups chopped bokchoy aka pechay (or your preferred greens)
4 tablespoons soy sauce
Salt and pepper to taste


DIRECTIONS:


Heat a medium pan over medium heat. Once hot, pour enough cooking oil to cover base of pan.


Fry the tofu until golden.


Mix in the garlic, onions, tomatoes, and a few pinches of salt and pepper. Cook until the onions have turned translucent.


Add the bean sprouts and mix well. Cook until they have softened.


Mix in the bokchoy/pechay. Season with soy sauce. Adjust seasoning to taste (it should be slightly extra savory if serving with rice).


Cook for another 3-5 minutes in very low heat. Mix occasionally.


Turn off the heat and serve hot with rice.
